node.text: Though her career began in classical music, painting, and analog photography, @HelenaGarza_'s field of inspiration is boundless. In this project, she shares a VR painting – a proposal of reality understood from figurative memories and the present environment in constant change and reconstruction. Learn more about her unique explorations in art at vans.com/offthewall

node.text: In late 2019, just before Covid-19 shut down live performances worldwide, we invited the crowd at @HouseOfVans London to get creative and help make a music video for @JPEGMAFIA. Watch the final edit and get to know the experimental rap artist at vans.com/offthewall

node.text: Vault by Vans and Aries present the “GO YOUR OWN WAY” footwear and apparel collection inspired by deadstock apparel and footwear. Founded by Sofia Prantera in 2010, Aries takes a subversive approach to streetwear and meets it with luxury and craftsmanship. The capsule features six footwear styles and a  fourteen-piece apparel and accessories offering launching  September 11, 2021. Visit vans.com/droplist for more info.

node.text: Take a step into the surreal landscape of Chloé Bernard’s (@chloyeah_suzzies) 3D Mural, created in an abandoned footbridge. Hailing from Marseille, France, Chloé gives us a glimpse into the fantastic spaces she dreams up in her mind. Get to know more about the tattooist, graphic designer, skateboarder and painter at vans.com/chloebernard

node.text: Artist, musician, and surfer, Alex Knost (@knostthankyou) has been experimenting in surfing’s subculture for over a decade. Regardless of the medium, he often challenges relationships between texture and color while breaking the regiment of art forms. Watch his film about surfing and the exploration of dissonant sound at vans.com/offthewall
